ters of concern" as Latour would have put it, laying bare modern-day "actors" and "networks" rather than reporting mere "matters of fact"? These questions are drawn into an inter-disciplinary discussion that addresses concerns and questions of epistemology, the sociology of knowledge as well as urban and documentary studies.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2019: Backlist Collection  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aANT. 4aActor-Network Theory. 4aBruno Latour. 4aCity. 4aDocumentary. 4aDocumenting Strategy. 4aEpistemology. 4aGeneral Literature Studies. 4aGlobal South. 4aKnowledge Production. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aMegacity. 4aNarrative. 4aRealism. 4aRepresentation. 4aSociology. 4aTheory of Literature. 4aUrban Cities. 4aUrban Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aANT.  aActor-Network Theory.  aBruno Latour.  aCity.  aDocumentary.  aDocumenting Strategy.  aEpistemology.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aGlobal South.  aKnowledge Production.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMegacity.  aNarrative.  aRealism.  aRepresentation.  aSociology.  aTheory of Literature.  aUrban Cities.  aUrban Studies.2 aKnowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2019: Backlist Collectionefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook